\begin_layout Part Introduction (ClassicThesis)
This chapter gives a brief review of all the basic concepts and previous
 work that this thesis is based on.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset

In section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chpt:models"

\end_inset

, we begin by introducing the frequent models of solvent in a simulation,
 from the simplest implicit continuum model to the most complex explicit
 one.
 The overview of these models then helps to understand the choice of description
 scale used in our study, as well as its limits.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset

Once the model is chosen, all the theories become mathematical problems.
 Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chpt:statistical-mechanics"

\end_inset

 reviews some basic concepts of statistical mechanics for liquids (i.e.
 theory of liquids), which present some brief formalisms deduced for an
 atomic solvent model.
 Two frontier approaches are introduced with a few deductions: the classical
 density functional theory (c
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{DFT}
\end_layout

\end_inset

), and the integral equation theory (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{IET}
\end_layout

\end_inset

).
 A mathematical equivalence between these two theories is also presented.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset

The following section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chpt:iem-mdft"

\end_inset

 gives the extension of the two theories to the molecular solvent case,
 i.e.
 the molecular density functional theory (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{MDFT}
\end_layout

\end_inset

) that this thesis works upon, and the molecular Ornstein-Zernike (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{MOZ}
\end_layout

\end_inset

) approach for 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{IET}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 The equivalence between these two theories gave us the idea to use the
 expansion techniques in 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{IET}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 to serve 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{MDFT}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset VSpace medskip
\end_inset

Section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "chpt:mdft"

\end_inset

 gives some supplementary presentation of the initial code 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
acs{MDFT}
\end_layout

\end_inset

, which the development of this thesis is based on.
\end_layout

